HTTP Methods in Postman
1. GET = Read/Get Data
2. POST = Create New Data
3. PUT = Update/Replace Full Data
4. PATCH = Update Partial Data
5. DELETE = Remove Data
6. HEAD = Headers Only(No Body)
7. OPTIONS = Allowed Method Info
8. TRACE = Test or Debug
9. CONNECT = Tunnel Connection

These are the main methods of Postman:
It's called CRUD:

C = CREATE  /  POST
R = READ    /  GET
U = UPDATE  /  PUT/PATCH
D = DELETE  /  DELETE
